  - STATE_UPDATE: {'last_reflection_result': '## Post-Mortem Analysis Summary\n\n**Attempt 3, Round 1 - Deterioration Score: 4/10**\n\n### Mandatory Checks\n| Check | Status |\n|-------|--------|\n| **Step 1 (Targets)** | ✅ PASS - Fuzzer targets correctly defined in build.sh |\n| **Step 2 (Infra Compliance)** | ✅ PASS - Dockerfile and build.sh properly structured |\n| **Step 6 (Runtime Stability)** | ❌ FAIL - Compilation error prevents binary creation |\n\n### Root Cause\nThe project uses **Go 1.25.7** (`go 1.25.7` in go.mod). In Go 1.25+, the Go toolchain is stored as a module under GOMODCACHE (`/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/`). The `go-118-fuzz-build` tool creates an overlay JSON that replaces `testing/fuzz.go`, but **Go 1.25+ does not allow overlay replacements beneath GOMODCACHE**, causing the build to panic.\n\n### Lesson Learned\nThe `go-118-fuzz-build` overlay mechanism is incompatible with Go 1.25+ due to the toolchain being stored under GOMODCACHE. The fix should either:\n1. **Patch `go-118-fuzz-build`** to skip the `testing/fuzz.go` overlay replacement for Go 1.25+\n2. **Downgrade the Go version** in `go.mod` to a compatible version (e.g., 1.24.x)\n\n### Backtracking Decision\n**No rollback needed.** Score is 4 (not > 7), no previous attempts to compare against, and no complexity/loop issues.'}
